The match was a closely fought affair, with both sides having chances to win. In the end, it was Mundle's goal that proved to be the difference. name: Rangers vs Ross County
summary: Rangers secured a resounding 6-0 victory over Ross County in the Scottish Premiership. The match was a one-sided affair, with Rangers dominating from start to finish. Fashion Sakala opened the scoring for Rangers in the 15th minute, before Malik Tillman doubled their lead just five minutes later. Alfredo Morelos made it 3-0 in the 34th minute, before James Sands extended their advantage in the 38th minute. Ross County were unable to mount any significant challenge, and Rangers continued to pile on the pressure in the second half. Antonio Colak scored the fifth goal in the 65th minute, before Tillman completed the rout with his second goal in the 85th minute. The win moved Rangers up to second place in the Premiership standings, while Ross County remained in 10th place.

name: Winter fuel payments pensioners
summary: Several news articles highlight the impact of recent changes to the Winter Fuel Payment scheme on UK pensioners. The BBC reports that pensioners are being urged to claim additional help as the payments have been cut. The Guardian and Sky News emphasize the government's campaign to promote Pension Credit, another form of financial assistance, as the Winter Fuel Payments have been restricted. The Telegraph notes that thousands of pensioners will receive their payments "too late" due to the changes. GB News explains how the changes have reduced energy bill support for pensioners by £300. Politically, The New Statesman and LabourList discuss potential discontent among Labour voters over the payment cuts, with one MP even suggesting the possibility of voting against the government on this issue.
